ared with her confidential, much franker, and very thorough Notes on the Health of the British Army, where the full horrors of disease and neglect are laid out, with the names of those responsible.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aCrimean WarxHistoryx19th CenturyxGreat Britian. 0aCrimean WarzGreat BritianxHistoryy19th Century. 0aCrimean War, 1853-1856vPersonal narratives, British. 0aCrimean War, 1853-1856xHealth aspects. 0aCrimean War, 1853-1856xMedical care. 0aCrimean War, 1853-1856xPersonal narratives, British. 0aHistory. 0aMilitary art and science. 0aNursing. 0aSoldiersxHealth and hygienexHistoryx19th centuryxGreat Britain. 0aSoldiersxHealth and hygienezGreat BritainxHistoryy19th century. 4aHistory. 4aHistory: Military History. 4aMedical: History Of Medicine. 4aSocial Science: Women’s Studies. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Medical.2bisacsh1 aMcDonald, Lynn, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2011-2010z978311127414008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2011 - 2010z978311127721940uhttps://doi.org/10.51644/978155458245740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781554582457423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781554582457/original  a978-3-11-127414-0  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2011-2010c2010d2011  a978-3-11-127721-9  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2011 - 2010c2010d2011  aGBV-deGruyter-alles